  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7038.54 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and the massive +13.2B gamma wall at 7050, dealers are currently in a neutral hedging zone but approaching heavy selling pressure. The PIN regime with 123.4B total GEX creates strong mean-reverting forces, and any push toward 7050 will trigger aggressive dealer selling as they hedge their long gamma positions. Watch for rejection at the 7050 wall and potential bounce support at 7030 (8.2B) if we pull back, with the 7015 negative gamma strike acting as a magnet below current levels.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy action with upside capped near 7050 and downside support around 7030.",
